# Frontend — React + TypeScript + Vite

- Function components + hooks only. One folder per module under `frontend/src/modules/<module>`
  with `pages/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, `api/`, `types.ts`.
- Data fetching through a typed API client per module (`api/`); never call `fetch` inline in a
  component. Handle loading / empty / error states explicitly (see 600-ui-design for copy).
- Routing: lazy-load module pages. Shared layout (Sidebar/Header/AppLayout) lives in
  `frontend/src/layout` and comes from `frontend/src/styles` tokens.
- State: local state + context for cross-cutting (auth, current user, theme). No global store
  unless justified.
- Strict TypeScript: no `any`; type API responses with DTunmatched-safe types.
- Accessibility floor: keyboard focus visible, labels on inputs, respects reduced motion.
- Keep the Pipedrive-like density: tables and the pipeline are the protagonists; analytics
  visuals (donut/heatmap/area) are reserved for Dashboards (Wave 2) — see 600-ui-design.
